<TITLE> New ministers vow to implement AL's polls pledges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 31 (bdnews24.com)The newly sworn-in ministers on Friday said they will put in their time and effort to implement the Awami League's campaign pledges. Shajahan Khan, the new shipping minister, told bdnews24.com, "I've been working for the people all along. I realise that holding a minister's portfolio equips one with myriad ways of serving the people." "I thank the prime minister for affording me such an opportunity to serve my nation." He pledged to clear the rivers of all illegal buildings and installations choking them. "Efforts to improve the marine as well as river-port facilities more effectively will be mounted." Elected from Madaripur-2 seat, the AL leader had spearheaded labour movements too. Set to take over the power and energy ministry, another new minister Enamul Haque told bdnews24.com, "All my life, I've been actively involved in pursuing [Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman's] political ideals. On this happy occasion, I remember Bangabandhu most." This former military officer won the polls on Awami League-led Grand Alliance ticket from Chanpainawabganj-1 seat. The new women and children affairs state minister Shirin Sharmin Chowdhury said, "I'll do my best to discharge the responsibilities vested with me." Shireen is an MP from the reserved women's seat. Elected an MP from Patuakhali-4 seat as a Grand Alliance candidate, Md Mahbubur Rahman said, "I feel grateful that I have been selected as a member of Sheikh Hasina's cabinet. I vow to work according to her directives." Set to be the state minister for cultural affairs, Promod Mankin was elected an MP from Mymensingh-1. Mojibur Rahman Fakir, the state minister earmarked for health and family welfare ministry, was elected from Mymensingh-3. The new minister and five state ministers laid flowers on Friday at National Memorial in Savar and observed a one-minute silence. Khan said his ministry will take steps to restore navigability to the rivers. Rahman said the proposed Tipaimukh Dam must be 